E4Plus1.uk.description: From Mo Gilligan to Joanna Lumley, what do Britain's favourite famous faces think of The Greatest Auction, Our Planet, Countdown, M3GAN, and Siren: Survive the Island? (S5 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Celebrity Gogglebox for Stand...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...Up To Cancer: Celebrities and Gogglebox regulars check out Rivals, First Dates, Only Connect and much more in this special episode for Stand Up To Cancer. (S24 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: On the 'Box this time: Sweetpea, Michael McIntyre's The Wheel, Will You Marry Me?, Deal or No Deal, I Love a Mama's Boy, National Parks from Above, This Morning and ITV News. (S24 Ep8) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Can Italian restaurateur Giovanni, who's 61, out-charm Fred? Can Jason see past prison officer Tyrone's ADHD? And does barber Chris smell good enough for dental nurse Debbie? (S12 Ep7) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: PR exec Claudia, who's 26, looks for a date who won't give her the ick. And 71-year-old music producer Barry dates a former member of a pop group. (S13 Ep5) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Celebrity Gogglebox for Stand...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...Up To Cancer: Celebrities and Gogglebox regulars check out Rivals, First Dates, Only Connect and much more in this special episode for Stand Up To Cancer. (S24 Ep7) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: On the 'Box this time: Sweetpea, Michael McIntyre's The Wheel, Will You Marry Me?, Deal or No Deal, I Love a Mama's Boy, National Parks from Above, This Morning and ITV News. (S24 Ep8) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Don't Tell the Bride
E4Plus1.uk.description: The One on a Caravan Site: Lauren wants to feel unique at her wedding, but her groom plans their nuptials at the same caravan park that Lauren visits every year...

E4Plus1.uk.title: Don't Tell the Bride
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Titanic One: Essex couple Jas and Bobby are heading for rocky waters. One of them wants a quiet wedding, while the other favours a Titanic-style night to remember.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks Omnibus
E4Plus1.uk.description: Theresa fears for her relationship. Sienna's attempts to build bridges backfire. Donny makes a desperate escape, while Gemma takes a dangerous gamble. And there's a mysterious sighting...

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: Cheeky original clips featuring ducks going up an escalator, animal impressions, a few narrow escapes on a snowboard and rally driving. Plus: an energy drink house prank and a butcher rap.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Wild: Mitch, Cam and Phil crash Jay's annual hiking trip to find an elusive bald eagle. And Gloria, Alex, Claire and Haley get together to plan a baby shower. (S10 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Stand by Your Man: Dylan and Luke are impressed by Bill's tales of heroism as a firefighter, which makes Phil feel emasculated. So he invites the guys over for male bonding. (S10 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Yes-Woman: To be less negative, Claire rebrands herself as the woman who says 'yes', and inadvertently approves of Luke's new relationship with a colleague. (S10 Ep19)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Can't Elope: Haley and Dylan's plan to quietly elope before the babies are born does not go as hoped. Jay tries to get his new business off the ground by courting an Insta celeb. (S10 Ep20)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Commencement: Cam finally gets a chance to shine when he's asked to preside over the high school graduation ceremony at the last minute, while Jay gives the commencement address. (S10 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Year of Birthdays: As the birth of Haley and Dylan's twins approaches, the family look back at how each of them celebrated their birthdays this past year. (S10 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Don't Tell the Bride
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Titanic One: Essex couple Jas and Bobby are heading for rocky waters. One of them wants a quiet wedding, while the other favours a Titanic-style night to remember.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Don't Tell the Bride
E4Plus1.uk.description: Sophia wants a blingy wedding. Love-struck groom Micky hopes to impress with a winter wonderland event. Will his wedding plan get a frosty reception?

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Leone's: Rose built her Italian restaurant in New Jersey into a thriving business, but when she spent two years in hospital, her son ran it into the ground. Can Gordon save it? (S5 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Burger Kitchen (Part 1/2): In the first half of a two-part Nightmare, Gordon tries to save a burger joint in LA, run by a dysfunctional family in a state of constant conflict. (S5 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Burger Kitchen (Part 2/2): In the second half of a two-part Nightmare in LA, can Gordon Ramsay bring together the fragmented Saffron family and save their failing restaurant? (S5 Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lisa the Beauty Queen: Lisa wins second place in a beauty contest. (S4 Ep4/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Marge Gets a Job: When Marge gets a job at the power plant, Mr Burns falls in love with her and invites her over to dinner, complete with a kidnapped Tom Jones to serenade them. (S4 Ep7/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: New Kid on the Block: When Homer gets kicked out of an all-you-can-eat seafood restaurant for eating too much, he takes the owner to court. (S4 Ep8/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lisa's First Word: The family try to get Maggie to say her first word. But Homer's glad that she hasn't spoken yet, because all Lisa and Bart do is talk back to him. (S4 Ep10/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homer's Triple Bypass: Homer has a heart attack while he's watching TV. The hospital says he needs a bypass, but Homer can't afford it. Of course, there's always Dr Nick... (S4 Ep11/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Treehouse of Horror Presents Simpsons Wicked This Way Comes: A mysterious tattoo-covered fella at the carnival tells Lisa three surreal stories. (S36 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Convenience Airways: The Simpsons endure a nightmare flight on Convenience Airways - the only airline in America that Homer's isn't banned from. (S36 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Live AFCON Final: Senegal v...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...Morocco: Host nation Morocco are desperate for a first AFCON title for 50 years. But an in-form Senegal - who lifted the trophy just four years ago - stand in their way.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Duke of Edinburgh Awards: Will is asked to co-ordinate the school's Duke of Edinburgh Award scheme and immediately turns the situation to his advantage. (S2 Ep5/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: End of Term: Will is stressed about exams, Jay has other things on his mind, Simon finally seems to be making headway with Carli, and Neil forgets his kit for his PE exam. (S2 Ep6/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Fashion Show: It's the start of term and Carli is organising a charity fashion show. It's only for the cool kids, so our heroes aren't involved - until a last-minute hitch. (S3 Ep1/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Gig and the Girlfriend: To impress a girl in the year below, Simon attends his first concert since he saw Take That with his mum. But Will, Jay and Neil tag along too. (S3 Ep2/6)

Film4.uk.description: (1999) David Lynch's fact-based drama with Richard Farnsworth. Alvin Straight drives hundreds of miles across the USA on a lawnmower to visit his dying brother - Harry Dean Stanton.

Film4.uk.title: Lynch/Oz

Film4.uk.description: (1951) Comedy adventure. Burt Lancaster stars as a Foreign Legion sergeant leading nine men on a dangerous mission to prevent a Berber attack on a North African desert fort.

Film4.uk.title: Gunman's Walk
Film4.uk.description: (1958) Western. Van Heflin stars as a veteran frontiersman whose determination to mould his sons in his gun-totin' image backfires disastrously. With Tab Hunter and James Darren.

Film4.uk.title: Tobruk
Film4.uk.description: (1967) World War II thriller. George Peppard, Rock Hudson and Nigel Green lead a daring Allied raid to destroy Nazi fuel dumps in North Africa.

Film4.uk.title: The Adjustment Bureau
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Romance meets sci-fi thriller. Matt Damon and Emily Blunt star as a politician and a dancer who begin to suspect that a shadowy group of men are interfering with their lives.

Film4.uk.title: The Great Wall
Film4.uk.description: (2017) Fantasy adventure starring Matt Damon and Willem Dafoe. In 11th-century China, Europeans seeking the secret of gunpowder are caught up in a war against alien monsters.

Film4.uk.title: John Wick: Chapter 3 - Parabellum
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Keanu Reeves returns for the third time as the supposedly retired hitman. Someone's put a contract on John Wick's head and only a mystic in Morocco can lift it.

Film4.uk.title: Rat Race
Film4.uk.description: (2001) Comedy. A Las Vegas casino-owner sets up a unique game for six punters: a race across America, hunting for $2m. Starring John Cleese, Rowan Atkinson and Whoopi Goldberg.

Film4.uk.title: Earth vs the Flying Saucers
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Sci-fi thriller. Hugh Marlowe stars as a scientist who discovers Earth is threatened by a fleet of flying saucers bent on global conquest. With special effects by Ray Harryhausen.

Film4.uk.title: Secret Headquarters

Film4.uk.title: Entrapment
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Action thriller. Sean Connery is Robert 'Mac' MacDougal, one of the world's finest art thieves, while Catherine Zeta-Jones is the insurance company agent out to trap him.

Film4.uk.title: Heat
Film4.uk.description: (1995) Al Pacino and Robert De Niro star in Michael Mann's crime thriller. A cop sets out to track down a career criminal and his gang of armed robbers. Violence/strong language.

Film4.uk.title: Firestarter
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Stephen King adaptation with Zac Efron. Superpowered parents try to protect their pyrokinetic daughter from a shadowy organisation. Can they stop her becoming a twisted fire starter?

Film4.uk.title: Little Monsters
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Undead comedy horror with Lupita Nyong'o. Can an infantile slacker, a diligent teacher and a deranged children's TV presenter rescue a school trip from a zombie outbreak? Head count!

Film4.uk.title: The Seventh Voyage of Sinbad

Film4.uk.title: Rosaline
